```text id="c9p5qe"
judge
characters
without
evidence
```

without understanding:

```text id="k4p8qe"
characters
change
through
events
```

Students may also think:

```text id="n6p3qe"
conflict
is
always
external
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="t1p7qe"
conflict
can be
internal
or external
```

Example:

character:

```text id="q5p2qe"
must decide
between honesty
and popularity
```

students may say:

```text id="v8p4qe"
no conflict
```

because no fight occurs,

instead of identifying:

```text id="a3p7qe"
internal
conflict
```

because:

```text id="g9p1rx"
conflict
involves
problems
and tension
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="w4p6qe"
narrative analysis
```

For Grade 6:

focus includes:

Plot:

* exposition
* rising action
* climax
* falling action
* resolution

Character:

* traits
* motivation
* development
* relationships
* decisions

Conflict:

* internal
* external
* character vs self
* character vs others
* resolution

